author: COMSOL
description:
Three studies are performed to show the properties of a NiTi alloy block subjected to uniaxial tension–compression loading, using the Souza–Auricchio model.

The first parametric study displays the pseudoelasticity effect at different temperatures. In the second study a partial loading–unloading cycle is added. Finally, a third study shows the shape memory effect in a low-temperature loading cycle followed by a temperature increase.
label: uniaxial_loading_of_shape_memory_alloy_souza_auricchio.mph
